<section>
  <div class="wrap split">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Once you arrive, an advocate works with you one-on-one to understand your situation and connect you with the right support — at your pace, and always confidentially.</p>
      <h2>Services available in shelter</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>One-on-one advocacy</strong> — addressing the impacts of violence and helping you plan next steps.</li>
        <li><strong>Support and educational groups</strong> — covering the dynamics of abuse, parenting, budgeting, and wellness.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal advocacy</strong> — help pursuing protective orders and understanding the legal process.</li>
        <li><strong>Safety planning</strong> — an advocate and client develop a plan that the client and children can use if an abusive situation arises.</li>
        <li><strong>Community resource referrals</strong> — connecting you to housing, employment, healthcare, and other services beyond our shelter.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:24px">All services are free, confidential, and available to survivors of all genders and abilities.</p>
